item.title: Anyone know which classes deal with connecting to the update server(485 client)
item.dc:creator: @semaphore semaphore
item.description:
@semaphore wrote:

Sure; I’ll elaborate. I agree (though less vehemently) with _frank.

If I remember correctly, 377 is where literal strings were removed. This also happens to be the last version of the old engine. I don’t have my archived sources in front of me, but I don’t recall anything spectacular happening in 420/421. I think around 450 something was the enhancement of their internal VM. (Which I’m waiting for them to further enhance)…

Unhandled: I really don’t think you did yourself a favor by speaking/replying. You indicated that you have at least read some posts, but make no mistake, tinkering around with a few posts and some other developer’s code does not make you an expert. It takes a long time for you to be able to wear the big-boy diapers and actually make fun of someone. It’s incredibly trite to say

[quote=“Unhandled, post:4, topic:181499”]…
Yes, it’s possible to disable to whole update server process
…[/quote]
I mean… come on, of course anything is possible. The real question; one that would imply truly abstract thought and understanding would be to ask whether it is a good idea to do so. It is simply more work than it is worth to end up with something that is only of clientside (or less) worth.

[/quote]
How would that help? The classes are are butchered up/static so that nothing is where it should be. Before 421 I think, the client class had most of the strings you’d see, now in 421+, they randomly strewn throughout the classes. amiwrong?

Yes, it’s possible to disable to whole update server process, but you’d want start refactoring so you have at least some idea what your doing. I’m taking it your not a moparscaper who wants a 485 clinet for ur pikkerisrlyleetscape servar?[/quote]
Not technically a moparscaper because i really dont like that site its full of idiots who dont know what the hell they are doing, But yes i am looking for a way to remove the update server process so that i can connect to a 481 server but i dont know if thats gonna work or not, ive read alot about it and someone has already logged in on a 484 client to a 481 server.
